26// For operators that are not supported on all platforms.
27class OptionalOperator final {
28 public:
29 OptionalOperator(bool supported, const Operator* op)
30 : supported_(supported), op_(op) {}
31
32 bool IsSupported() const { return supported_; }
33 // Gets the operator only if it is supported.
34 const Operator* op() const {
35 DCHECK(supported_);
36 return op_;
37 }
38 // Always gets the operator, even for unsupported operators. This is useful to
39 // use the operator as a placeholder in a graph, for instance.
40 const Operator* placeholder() const { return op_; }
41
42 private:
43 bool supported_;
44 const Operator* const op_;
45};

296template <const int simd_size = kSimd128Size,
297 typename = std::enable_if_t<simd_size == kSimd128Size ||
298 simd_size == kSimd256Size>>
299class SimdImmediateParameter {
300 public:
301 explicit SimdImmediateParameter(const uint8_t immediate[simd_size]) {
302 std::copy(immediate, immediate + simd_size, immediate_.begin());
303 }
304 SimdImmediateParameter() = default;
305 const std::array<uint8_t, simd_size>& immediate() const { return immediate_; }
306 const uint8_t* data() const { return immediate_.data(); }
307 uint8_t operator[](int x) const { return immediate_[x]; }
308
309 private:
310 std::array<uint8_t, simd_size> immediate_;
311};
312
313using S128ImmediateParameter = SimdImmediateParameter<kSimd128Size>;
314using S256ImmediateParameter = SimdImmediateParameter<kSimd256Size>;
315
316template <const int simd_size>
317V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE inline bool operator==(
318 SimdImmediateParameter<simd_size> const& lhs,
319 SimdImmediateParameter<simd_size> const& rhs) {
320 return (lhs.immediate() == rhs.immediate());
321}
322
323template <const int simd_size>
324bool operator!=(SimdImmediateParameter<simd_size> const& lhs,
325 SimdImmediateParameter<simd_size> const& rhs) {
326 return !(lhs == rhs);
327}
328
329template <const int simd_size>
330size_t hash_value(SimdImmediateParameter<simd_size> const& p) {
331 return base::hash_range(p.immediate().begin(), p.immediate().end());
332}
333
334template <const int simd_size>
335V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE inline std::ostream& operator<<(
336 std::ostream& os, SimdImmediateParameter<simd_size> const& p) {
337 for (int i = 0; i < simd_size; i++) {
338 const char* separator = (i < simd_size - 1) ? "," : "";
339 os << static_cast<uint32_t>(p[i]) << separator;
340 }
341 return os;
342}

352// ShiftKind::kShiftOutZeros means that it is guaranteed that the bits shifted
353// out of the left operand are all zeros. If this is not the case, undefined
354// behavior (i.e., incorrect optimizations) will happen.
355// This is mostly useful for Smi untagging.
356enum class ShiftKind { kNormal, kShiftOutZeros };
357
358size_t hash_value(ShiftKind);
359V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream&, ShiftKind);
360ShiftKind ShiftKindOf(Operator const*) V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT;
361
362// TruncateKind::kSetOverflowToMin sets the result of a saturating float-to-int
363// conversion to INT_MIN if the conversion returns INT_MAX due to overflow. This
364// makes it easier to detect an overflow. This parameter is ignored on platforms
365// like x64 and ia32 where a range overflow does not result in INT_MAX.
366enum class TruncateKind { kArchitectureDefault, kSetOverflowToMin };
367std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, TruncateKind kind);
368size_t hash_value(TruncateKind kind);

370// Interface for building machine-level operators. These operators are
371// machine-level but machine-independent and thus define a language suitable
372// for generating code to run on architectures such as ia32, x64, arm, etc.
373class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE MachineOperatorBuilder final
374 : public NON_EXPORTED_BASE(ZoneObject) {
375 public:
376 // Flags that specify which operations are available. This is useful
377 // for operations that are unsupported by some back-ends.
378 enum Flag : unsigned {
379 kNoFlags = 0u,
380 kFloat32RoundDown = 1u << 0,
381 kFloat64RoundDown = 1u << 1,
382 kFloat32RoundUp = 1u << 2,
383 kFloat64RoundUp = 1u << 3,
384 kFloat32RoundTruncate = 1u << 4,
385 kFloat64RoundTruncate = 1u << 5,
386 kFloat32RoundTiesEven = 1u << 6,
387 kFloat64RoundTiesEven = 1u << 7,
388 kFloat64RoundTiesAway = 1u << 8,
389 kInt32DivIsSafe = 1u << 9,
390 kUint32DivIsSafe = 1u << 10,
391 kWord32ShiftIsSafe = 1u << 11,
392 kWord32Ctz = 1u << 12,
393 kWord64Ctz = 1u << 13,
394 kWord64CtzLowerable = 1u << 14,
395 kWord32Popcnt = 1u << 15,
396 kWord64Popcnt = 1u << 16,
397 kWord32ReverseBits = 1u << 17,
398 kWord64ReverseBits = 1u << 18,
399 kFloat32Select = 1u << 19,
400 kFloat64Select = 1u << 20,
401 kInt32AbsWithOverflow = 1u << 21,
402 kInt64AbsWithOverflow = 1u << 22,
403 kWord32Rol = 1u << 23,
404 kWord64Rol = 1u << 24,
405 kWord64RolLowerable = 1u << 25,
406 kSatConversionIsSafe = 1u << 26,
407 kWord32Select = 1u << 27,
408 kWord64Select = 1u << 28,
409 kLoadStorePairs = 1u << 29,
410 kAllOptionalOps =
411 kFloat32RoundDown | kFloat64RoundDown | kFloat32RoundUp |
412 kFloat64RoundUp | kFloat32RoundTruncate | kFloat64RoundTruncate |
413 kFloat64RoundTiesAway | kFloat32RoundTiesEven | kFloat64RoundTiesEven |
414 kWord32Ctz | kWord64Ctz | kWord64CtzLowerable | kWord32Popcnt |
415 kWord64Popcnt | kWord32ReverseBits | kWord64ReverseBits |
416 kInt32AbsWithOverflow | kInt64AbsWithOverflow | kWord32Rol |
417 kWord64Rol | kWord64RolLowerable | kSatConversionIsSafe |
418 kFloat32Select | kFloat64Select | kWord32Select | kWord64Select |
419 kLoadStorePairs
420 };
421 using Flags = base::Flags<Flag, unsigned>;
422
423 class AlignmentRequirements {
424 public:
425 enum UnalignedAccessSupport { kNoSupport, kSomeSupport, kFullSupport };
426
427 bool IsUnalignedLoadSupported(MachineRepresentation rep) const {
428 return IsUnalignedSupported(unalignedLoadUnsupportedTypes_, rep);
429 }
430
431 bool IsUnalignedStoreSupported(MachineRepresentation rep) const {
432 return IsUnalignedSupported(unalignedStoreUnsupportedTypes_, rep);
433 }
434
435 static AlignmentRequirements FullUnalignedAccessSupport() {
436 return AlignmentRequirements(kFullSupport);
437 }
438 static AlignmentRequirements NoUnalignedAccessSupport() {
439 return AlignmentRequirements(kNoSupport);
440 }
441 static AlignmentRequirements SomeUnalignedAccessUnsupported(
442 base::EnumSet<MachineRepresentation> unalignedLoadUnsupportedTypes,
443 base::EnumSet<MachineRepresentation> unalignedStoreUnsupportedTypes) {
444 return AlignmentRequirements(kSomeSupport, unalignedLoadUnsupportedTypes,
445 unalignedStoreUnsupportedTypes);
446 }
447
448 private:
449 explicit AlignmentRequirements(
450 AlignmentRequirements::UnalignedAccessSupport unalignedAccessSupport,
451 base::EnumSet<MachineRepresentation> unalignedLoadUnsupportedTypes =
452 base::EnumSet<MachineRepresentation>(),
453 base::EnumSet<MachineRepresentation> unalignedStoreUnsupportedTypes =
454 base::EnumSet<MachineRepresentation>())
455 : unalignedSupport_(unalignedAccessSupport),
456 unalignedLoadUnsupportedTypes_(unalignedLoadUnsupportedTypes),
457 unalignedStoreUnsupportedTypes_(unalignedStoreUnsupportedTypes) {}
458
459 bool IsUnalignedSupported(base::EnumSet<MachineRepresentation> unsupported,
460 MachineRepresentation rep) const {
461 // All accesses of bytes in memory are aligned.
462 DCHECK_NE(MachineRepresentation::kWord8, rep);
463 switch (unalignedSupport_) {
464 case kFullSupport:
465 return true;
466 case kNoSupport:
467 return false;
468 case kSomeSupport:
469 return !unsupported.contains(rep);
470 }
471 UNREACHABLE();
472 }
473
474 const AlignmentRequirements::UnalignedAccessSupport unalignedSupport_;
475 const base::EnumSet<MachineRepresentation> unalignedLoadUnsupportedTypes_;
476 const base::EnumSet<MachineRepresentation> unalignedStoreUnsupportedTypes_;
477 };

629 // These operators change the representation of numbers while preserving the
630 // value of the number. Narrowing operators assume the input is representable
631 // in the target type and are *not* defined for other inputs.
632 // Use narrowing change operators only when there is a static guarantee that
633 // the input value is representable in the target value.
634 //
635 // Some operators can have the behaviour on overflow change through specifying
636 // TruncateKind. The exact semantics are documented in the tests in
637 // test/cctest/compiler/test-run-machops.cc .
